    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>To set the <code>i</code>th element in <code>result</code> to the <code>i</code>th element in <code>newarray</code>, do the following:</p>\n<pre><code>result[i] = newarray[i];\n</code></pre>\n<p>In addition, you can copy over the entirety of the array using <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/System.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>arraycopy</code></a>:</p>\n<pre><code>System.arraycopy(newarray, 0, result, 0, newarray.length);\n</code></pre>\n<h3>See also:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/arrays.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Arrays - The Java™ Tutorials</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.java-samples.com/showtutorial.php?tutorialid=343\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">arraycopy() in Java</a></li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 126317,
      "reputation" : 4727,
      "user_id" : 322738,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 75,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4e51620640a9e6b4fae81b1189a41e37?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Rafael Steil",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/322738/rafael-steil"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1322484484,
    "creation_date" : 1322484484,
    "answer_id" : 8296025,
    "question_id" : 8295999,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use <code>System.arrayCopy</code> to copy arrays. Example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.arraycopy(newarray, 0, result, 0, newarray.length)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The first argument is the source array, then the source position, then the destination array and destination position, and the length. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1055220,
